{# purpose: document cover: the document-type kicker and the title #}
{# The `<dl>` of Author/Date/Version was removed in 4.0.0. Those three facts
   were composed into every document whether or not they meant anything: the
   author was whatever `git config user.name` returned, the date was the day
   the skeleton was generated rather than the day the content was written, and
   the version sat at 0.1 forever unless someone remembered to bump it. A fact
   nobody maintains is worse than an absent one, because a reader trusts it.
   Documents that genuinely track revisions use [[change-history]], which is
   dated per row and actually kept current. #}
{% macro metadata_header(type_name, title) %}
  <header class="doc-meta">
    <p class="doc-type">{{ type_name }}</p>
    <h1>{{ title }}</h1>
  </header>
{% endmacro %}
